The article is a Presidential Proclamation issued by President Barack Obama on January 20, 2010. The proclamation declares January 21 as National Angel Island Day, commemorating the opening of the Angel Island Immigration Station in San Francisco Bay a hundred years prior. The proclamation acknowledges the struggles faced by immigrants who arrived at Angel Island and were unjustly confined for months or years due to racially prejudiced immigration laws. It recognizes the contributions of those who were allowed entry and gained citizenship, and honors the immigrant experience and the history of Angel Island. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to learn more about Angel Island's history and to observe the anniversary with appropriate ceremonies and activities.